        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 4:01PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 400 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 8 miles south of Wild Horse Point, or 32 miles north of
La Junta, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sugar City, Haswell, Blue Lake, and Arlington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
